Q3.What is Overfitting and Underfitting? Explain techniques to avoid them.

->Overfitting means working well with the train data and not working well with the Test data.
    is known as overfitting.
->Underfitting means not working well with the train data and also and working well with the Test data.
    is known as Underfitting.
->Regularization is a technique used to solve the overfitting problem.
    It is used to increase the test accuracy. and decrease the train accuracy because test accuracy is important.

->Regularization is a techniques are Ridge(L2) and Lasso(L1):
    -These techniques are PENALIZE the line to the test data.
    -In Ridge the m values are close to the ZERO but not became zero. Because in formula their is a square.
    -In Lasso their is a chance to became m values zeros. because in formula their is no square. variance 0 columns are removed. This is also known as FEATURE_SELECTION.
    -Instead of using original m values. We can use Lasso m values and do prediction.
