Q5.What is Feature Scaling? Explain:
•	StandardScaler
•	MinMaxScaler
•	RobustScaler

->StandardScaler is used to scale down the values from 0 to 1. StandardScaler range is from 0 to 1.
    we will scale down the values because to get the accuracy predictions. Means Before scale down model think higher values columns are more
    important than the lower values column. So after scale down model will think all column are equal. and model train in best way and gives
    correct predictions.
    FORMULA: (X-mean)/std

->MinMaxScaler is used to scale down the values. this techniques same as StandardScaler but formula is different
    here the values are replaced by using the formula.
    Formula:
            (x-x.min) / (x.max-x.min)

->RobustScaler is used to scale down the  values based on the median and IQR
        formula:
                (X-median) / IQR
